    "steps": [
        "Preheat the ^oven$ to 400Â°F",
        "For the tofu, chop the tofu into 4 layers. Then cut each layer into 6 matchsticks. Set aside.",
        "Mix the sriracha, soy sauce, rice vinegar, honey, pepper, garlic powder, and oil in a ^medium sized bowl$. Toss the tofu matchsticks in the sauce to evenly coat. Be delicate to ensure the tofu stays in tact. Place on ^sheet pan$ lined with ^foil$. Put the sheet in the oven and bake for 10-15 minutes, or until it starts to brown. <i>To get the tofu crisp, set the oven to broil and broil for 1-3 minutes.</i>",
        "For the peanut sauce, mix the peanut butter, soy sauce, rice vinegar, honey, ginger, sriracha, red pepper flake, and lime juice together using a ^whisk$. If the sauce is to thick add the !water. Add additional water until desired consistency is reached. Taste and adjust to your liking.",
        "For the spring rolls, add the water to a ^9 inch cake pan$. Dip 1 sheet of the rice paper into the water and soak for 30 seconds. Lift and let the excess water drip off. Place on a plate. Add 3 leaves of arugula, 3 slices of banana pepper, carrot, avocado, and 3 pieces of tofu to the sheet. Roll the spring roll like a burrito. Set aside and repeat.",
